<div class="col-lg-10 col-lg-offset-1 col-md-12">
  <h2>Options</h2>
  
  <h3>Environment Options</h3>
  
  <p><code>ember-highlight-code</code> uses Ember CLI environment settings to include the styles for highlighting. This prevents the need for unnecessary styles being added to your vendor.css. To include your desired style add:</p>
  
  {{#ember-highlight-code language="javascript"}}
    'ember-highlight-code': {
      style: 'tomorrow'
    }    
  {{/ember-highlight-code}}
  
  <hr>
  
  <dl class="dl-horizontal">
    <dt>style</dt>
    <dd>The code highlight style you want <code>ember-highlight-code</code> to use. To use a style, include the <em>lower-case dasherized</em> style name from the following demo: <a href="https://highlightjs.org/static/demo/" target="_blank">highlight.js demo</a></dd>
    <dt><span class="small text-muted">string</span></dt>
    <dd><code>"tomorrow"</code></dd>
  </dl>

  <h3>Component Options</h3>
  <hr>
  <dl class="dl-horizontal">
    <dt>language</dt>
    <dd>The syntax for the code block. Available syntax: <a href="https://highlightjs.org/static/demo/" target="_blank">highlight.js demo</a></dd>
    <dt><span class="small text-muted">string</span></dt>
    <dd><code>""</code></dd>

    <dd class="clearfix">&nbsp;</dd>

    <dt>addLineNumbers</dt>
    <dd>Whether or not to add line numbers to the highlighted code block.</dd>
    <dt><span class="small text-muted">boolean</span></dt>
    <dd><code>false</code></dd>
  </dl>
</div>

